# tokens.rules.mdc

### A. Purpose
Define how design tokens are structured, referenced, and consumed across all Khwarizmi products. Tokens are the single source of truth for all visual values.

### B. Rules
- All design decisions (color, spacing, typography, radius, shadow, opacity) MUST be expressed as tokens.
- Token naming convention: `--{category}-{namespace}-{role}-{modifier}` (e.g. `--color-sf-primary-opacity-8`).
- Token categories:
  - `color` — all color values
  - `spacing` — all margin/padding values (defined in spacing.rules.md)
  - `typography` — font size, weight, line-height
  - `radius` — border radius values
  - `shadow` — elevation shadows
  - `opacity` — transparency levels
  - `zindex` — layering system
- Token sources:
  - Light mode: `material3-tokens.json`
  - Dark mode: `material3-dark-tokens.json`
  - CSS variables: `css-variables.css`
- CSS variable format uses comma-separated RGB values (e.g. `103,80,164`) — always wrap in `rgba()` when used in CSS.
- Tokens with opacity suffix (e.g. `-opacity-8`) include the alpha value in their JSON definition — use them as-is.
- Border radius token scale:
  - `--radius-none`: 0px
  - `--radius-xs`: 2px
  - `--radius-sm`: 4px
  - `--radius-md`: 8px
  - `--radius-lg`: 12px
  - `--radius-xl`: 16px
  - `--radius-full`: 9999px (pills, avatars)
- Elevation/shadow tokens:
  - `--shadow-sm`: `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)`
  - `--shadow-md`: `0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.12)`
  - `--shadow-lg`: `0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.16)`
  - `--shadow-xl`: `0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.20)`
- Tokens must never be overridden inline in component code.
- New tokens require design system team approval before use.

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- ✅ Reference tokens by their semantic name, not their value.
- ✅ Use `--color-sf-primary` not `rgb(103,80,164)`.
- ✅ Keep light and dark token sets in sync — every light token must have a dark counterpart.
- ✅ Use opacity tokens for hover, pressed, disabled, and overlay states.
- ✅ Use `--radius-md` (8px) as default for cards, inputs, buttons.

**Don't:**
- ❌ Do not hardcode any visual value that has a token equivalent.
- ❌ Do not create component-local color variables.
- ❌ Do not use box shadows outside the defined elevation scale.
- ❌ Do not modify token values per product — tokens are shared system-wide.
- ❌ Do not use opacity via `rgba()` directly when an opacity token exists.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating components, resolve every color, spacing, radius, and shadow from the token files.
- Map `material3-tokens.json` properties to CSS variable names by stripping the `$` prefix.
- Wrap all color token values in `rgba(VAL, ALPHA)` when writing CSS.
- When a dark mode context is detected (`.e-dark-mode`), switch to `material3-dark-tokens.json` values.
- Flag any use case where no token exists — do not invent values.

